The paper deals with the problem of joint state and parameter estimation in dynamic Bayesian networks, which is a core problem in machine learning and statistics. The proposed algorithm is a hybrid of particle filtering and assumed density filtering, which are commonly used in the fields of probabilistic inference and control theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
